Something RE: the famous Dr. Ray Peat anti-endotoxin carrot salad. He always recommended some olive oil for "taste" on top of the antibacterial coconut oil, but if you keep in mind the Dr. Walter Alvarez experiments on appetizing food being digested more vigorously, it makes a...

... lot of sense, a more vigorous peristalsis will lead to the insoluble fibre getting to "scrub" the intestine better, probably making it more effective. Never underestimate Taste in medicine and nutrition. Probably also why antibiotics are more effective together with sugar.

Talking about antibiotics, if you're taking something like Minocycline, it's also going to be more potent taken together with the carrot salad. Also same logic for recommendation of bamboo shoots (also undigestible fiber like carrots) being best eaten with cheese sauce type dish.

It's not THAT important, just something that became part of the forum culture, even just chewing a raw carrot is also ok. But generally people who suggest lengthwise will also tell you not to chew it too much lol
